#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:44
msgid "Philosophy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:46
msgid ""
"Vyper prioritizes three properties: security, simplicity, and auditability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:48
msgid ""
"To achieve these properties, Vyper excludes features that obscure control "
"flow or make code difficult to reason about. Each omission is a deliberate "
"tradeoff: less flexibility in exchange for explicit behavior. See :ref:"
"`Principles <design-principles>` for the full rationale."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:51
msgid "No Modifiers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:53
msgid "Solidity modifiers wrap function execution:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:55
msgid ""
"modifier onlyOwner() {\n"
"    require(msg.sender == owner, \"Not owner\");\n"
"    _;\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"function withdraw() public onlyOwner {\n"
"    // ...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:66
msgid ""
"While ``onlyOwner`` appears simple, modifiers can execute code before and "
"after the function body, modify state, and obscure the actual logic. "
"Understanding a function requires reading the modifier definitions elsewhere "
"in the codebase. For this reason, Vyper does not have modifiers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:68
msgid "In Vyper, checks are written inline:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:70
msgid ""
"@external\n"
"def withdraw():\n"
"    assert msg.sender == self.owner, \"Not owner\"\n"
"    # ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:77
msgid "Inline checks keep the control flow visible from top to bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:83
msgid "Modules Instead of Inheritance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:85
msgid ""
"Solidity supports multiple inheritance, which introduces the diamond problem "
"and C3 linearization complexity. Vyper replaces inheritance with a module "
"system that achieves the same goals of code reuse and behavioral "
"customization through different, more explicit mechanisms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:87
msgid "In Vyper 0.4.0, a module system was introduced for powerful code reuse:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:89
msgid ""
"import ownable\n"
"\n"
"initializes: ownable\n"
"exports: ownable.transfer_ownership\n"
"\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__():\n"
"    ownable.__init__()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:100
msgid ""
"Three declarations manage module relationships: ``initializes`` (this "
"contract manages the module's storage), ``uses`` (this contract reads module "
"state without initializing), and ``exports`` (expose module functions in the "
"ABI). See :doc:`using-modules` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:102
msgid ""
"Where Solidity uses ``abstract contract`` with ``virtual`` / ``override`` "
"for polymorphism, Vyper uses ``@abstract`` and ``@override`` decorators on "
"internal module functions. An abstract module declares methods with no "
"implementation; the module that ``initializes`` it supplies the concrete "
"``@override``. Each abstract module has exactly one initializer, so there is "
"no ambiguity about which override is chosen. All overrides are resolved at "
"compile time — there is no virtual dispatch and no method-resolution order. "
"See :ref:`abstract-modules` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:104
msgid ""
"A contract can be understood by reading one file and its direct imports; "
"dependencies and what is exposed in the external function table are explicit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:107
msgid "No Inline Assembly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:109
msgid ""
"Vyper excludes inline assembly. For low-level operations, use the :ref:"
"`built-in functions <built_in_functions>`: ``raw_call``, ``raw_create``, "
"``create_minimal_proxy_to``, ``create_from_blueprint``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:111
msgid ""
"Assembly bypasses compiler safety checks: type verification, overflow "
"protection, memory safety, and requires reviewers to reason about raw "
"opcodes. Vyper's built-in functions provide low-level access through "
"explicit, auditable function calls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:114
msgid "No Function Overloading"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:116
msgid ""
"Solidity permits multiple functions with the same name and different "
"parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:118
msgid ""
"function transfer(address to, uint256 amount) public { }\n"
"function transfer(address to, uint256 amount, bytes data) public { }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:123
msgid ""
"Vyper requires unique function names, keeping the ABI and call sites "
"explicit during review."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:126
msgid "No Operator Overloading"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:128
msgid ""
"``a + b`` always performs arithmetic addition. Operators cannot be redefined "
"for custom types, so operator behavior is consistent across the codebase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:131
msgid "No Infinite Loops"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:133
msgid "Vyper requires all loops to have a compile-time upper bound:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:135
msgid ""
"for i: uint256 in range(100):\n"
"    # Loop body\n"
"\n"
"# Variable count, but capped at compile time\n"
"for i: uint256 in range(count, bound=100):\n"
"    # Loop body"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:144
msgid ""
"Unbounded storage iteration can exceed the block gas limit, making contracts "
"unusable. Bounded loops prevent this class of issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:148
msgid ""
"Vyper's bounded loops and lack of recursion make gas costs statically "
"analyzable—every function call has a calculable upper bound (see :ref:"
"`design-principles`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:151
msgid "No Recursion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:153
msgid ""
"Functions cannot call themselves, directly or through intermediate "
"functions. Recursive logic must be converted to bounded iteration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:155
msgid ""
"This constraint keeps the call graph acyclic and analyzable at compile time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:158
msgid "Bounded Dynamic Arrays"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:160
msgid "Storage arrays require a maximum size at compile time:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:162
msgid "balances: DynArray[uint256, 100]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:166
msgid ""
"This keeps gas costs predictable and can prevent denial-of-service attacks. "
"For unbounded collections, use :ref:`HashMap <types>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:170
msgid "Explicit Type Conversions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:172
msgid "Vyper requires explicit type conversions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:174
msgid ""
"x: uint256 = 100\n"
"y: int256 = convert(x, int256)\n"
"\n"
"addr: address = 0x1234...\n"
"num: uint160 = convert(addr, uint160)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:182
msgid ""
"Vyper allows safe automatic widening (e.g., ``uint8`` to ``uint256``) but "
"requires explicit ``convert()`` for potentially lossy or semantically "
"significant conversions, such as signed/unsigned, addresses to integers, or "
"narrowing types. See :ref:`types` for the complete type reference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:185
msgid "Decimal Type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:187
msgid "Native base-10 fixed-point arithmetic with 10 fractional digits:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:189
msgid ""
"a: decimal = 0.1\n"
"b: decimal = 0.2\n"
"total: decimal = a + b  # exactly 0.3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:195
msgid ""
"Values like ``0.1`` and ``0.2`` cannot be represented exactly in binary "
"floating point, but Vyper's base-10 decimal type handles them precisely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:197
msgid ""
"Solidity lacks a native fixed-point type, requiring manual integer scaling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:200
msgid "Bounds Checking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:202
msgid ""
"Array accesses and arithmetic are bounds-checked at runtime. Out-of-bounds "
"access reverts. Integer overflow reverts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:204
msgid ""
"Solidity 0.8+ provides similar overflow protection, which is disabled in "
"``unchecked`` blocks. In Vyper, there is no way to disable the checks. For "
"cases where wrapping behavior is needed, there are explicit :ref:`unsafe_* "
"builtins <built_in_functions>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:207
msgid "Reentrancy Protection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:209
msgid "Built-in ``@nonreentrant`` decorator:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:211
msgid ""
"@external\n"
"@nonreentrant\n"
"def withdraw():\n"
"    # Cannot be re-entered"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:218
msgid ""
"The compiler generates the mutex. No manual reentrancy guard implementation "
"required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:222
msgid ""
"The 2016 DAO hack exploited reentrancy to drain ~$60M in ETH. This led to "
"the Ethereum hard fork that created Ethereum Classic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:224
msgid ""
"The ``extcall`` keyword makes external call sites explicit and easy to spot "
"during code review. Note that ``@nonreentrant`` is opt-in and uses a global "
"lock that protects against same-contract reentrancy: if any "
"``@nonreentrant`` function is executing, no other ``@nonreentrant`` function "
"in the same contract can be entered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:226
msgid ""
"Alternatively, ``#pragma nonreentrancy`` enables reentrancy protection by "
"default for all functions in the contract, so ``@nonreentrant`` is only "
"needed when not using the pragma. It does not prevent cross-contract "
"reentrancy (i.e., contract A calling contract B which calls back into "
"contract A). See :ref:`control-structures` for details on the lock behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:229
msgid "Syntax Differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:231
msgid "Practical syntax translations for common patterns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:235
msgid ""
"Every Vyper file must start with a version pragma: ``#pragma version "
"^0.4.0``. This is similar to Solidity's ``pragma solidity ^0.8.0;`` but uses "
"a comment syntax. Vyper files use the ``.vy`` extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:238
msgid "State Variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:240 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:259
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:281 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:302
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:330 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:347
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:367 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:397
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:420 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:446
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:473
msgid "Solidity:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:242
msgid ""
"uint256 public counter;\n"
"address private owner;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:247 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:267
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:289 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:312
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:337 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:374
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:404 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:431
#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:457 ../../../solidity-differences.rst:480
msgid "Vyper:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:249
msgid ""
"counter: public(uint256)\n"
"owner: address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:254
msgid ""
"Variables are private by default. Use ``public()`` to generate a getter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:257
msgid "Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:261
msgid ""
"function deposit() external payable returns (uint256) {\n"
"    return msg.value;\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:269
msgid ""
"@external\n"
"@payable\n"
"def deposit() -> uint256:\n"
"    return msg.value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:276
msgid ""
"Decorators specify visibility (``@external``, ``@internal``) and mutability "
"(``@payable``, ``@view``, ``@pure``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:279
msgid "Constructor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:283
msgid ""
"constructor(address _owner) {\n"
"    owner = _owner;\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:291
msgid ""
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__(owner: address):\n"
"    self.owner = owner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:297
msgid "The ``@deploy`` decorator marks the constructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:300
msgid "Events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:304
msgid ""
"event Transfer(address indexed from, address indexed to, uint256 value);\n"
"\n"
"function _transfer(address to, uint256 amount) internal {\n"
"    emit Transfer(msg.sender, to, amount);\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:314
msgid ""
"event Transfer:\n"
"    sender: indexed(address)\n"
"    receiver: indexed(address)\n"
"    amount: uint256\n"
"\n"
"@internal\n"
"def _transfer(to: address, amount: uint256):\n"
"    log Transfer(msg.sender, to, amount)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:325
msgid "``log`` instead of ``emit``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:328
msgid "Mappings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:332
msgid ""
"mapping(address => uint256) public balances;\n"
"mapping(address => mapping(address => uint256)) public allowances;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:339
msgid ""
"balances: public(HashMap[address, uint256])\n"
"allowances: public(HashMap[address, HashMap[address, uint256]])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:345
msgid "Interfaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:349
msgid ""
"interface IERC20 {\n"
"    function transfer(address to, uint256 amount) external returns (bool);\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:355
msgid "Vyper (inline declaration):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:357
msgid ""
"interface IERC20:\n"
"    def transfer(to: address, amount: uint256) -> bool: nonpayable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:362
msgid ""
"Interfaces can also be defined in separate ``.vyi`` files (see :ref:"
"`interfaces`). Vyper ships with built-in interfaces for ERC20, ERC721, etc. "
"via ``from ethereum.ercs import IERC20``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:365
msgid "Error Handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:369
msgid ""
"require(amount > 0, \"Amount must be positive\");\n"
"revert(\"Operation failed\");"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:376
msgid ""
"assert amount > 0, \"Amount must be positive\"\n"
"raise \"Operation failed\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:381
msgid "``assert`` for conditions, ``raise`` to revert."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:384
msgid "Self Reference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:386
msgid "State variables require ``self.`` prefix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:388
msgid "self.counter = self.counter + 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:392
msgid ""
"Storage access is always explicit. Since storage operations cost more gas "
"than memory operations, this distinction surfaces gas-intensive operations "
"during review."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:395
msgid "External Calls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:399
msgid ""
"IERC20(token).transfer(to, amount);\n"
"uint256 balance = IERC20(token).balanceOf(address(this));"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:406
msgid ""
"extcall IERC20(token).transfer(to, amount)\n"
"balance: uint256 = staticcall IERC20(token).balanceOf(self)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:411
msgid ""
"``extcall`` for state-changing calls, ``staticcall`` for view/pure "
"functions. The keywords make external calls and potential reentrancy points "
"visible in code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:415
msgid ""
"The ``extcall`` keyword is required for all state-changing external calls. "
"There is no implicit external call syntax in Vyper: every external call is "
"syntactically marked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:418
msgid "Structs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:422
msgid ""
"struct Person {\n"
"    string name;\n"
"    uint256 age;\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"Person public owner;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:433
msgid ""
"struct Person:\n"
"    name: String[64]\n"
"    age: uint256\n"
"\n"
"owner: public(Person)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:441
msgid ""
"Note that Vyper strings require explicit maximum length (``String[64]``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:444
msgid "Constants and Immutables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:448
msgid ""
"uint256 constant FEE = 100;\n"
"address immutable owner;\n"
"\n"
"constructor() {\n"
"    owner = msg.sender;\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:459
msgid ""
"FEE: constant(uint256) = 100\n"
"owner: immutable(address)\n"
"\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__():\n"
"    owner = msg.sender"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:468
msgid ""
"``constant`` values are inlined at compile time. ``immutable`` values are "
"set once during deployment and cannot be changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:471
msgid "Default Function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:475
msgid ""
"fallback() external payable { }\n"
"receive() external payable { }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:482
msgid ""
"@external\n"
"@payable\n"
"def __default__():\n"
"    pass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:489
msgid ""
"Vyper uses a single ``__default__`` function for both fallback and receive. "
"It executes when no other function matches or when receiving plain ETH."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:492
msgid "Why Vyper?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:494
msgid "Use Vyper if:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:496
msgid "**You have Python experience.** The syntax is familiar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:497
msgid ""
"**You want compiler-enforced constraints.** The compiler rejects unbounded "
"loops, implicit conversions, and recursive calls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:498
msgid ""
"**You prefer explicit code.** One way to do most things. No modifiers, no "
"inheritance, no operator overloading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../solidity-differences.rst:499
msgid ""
"**You want no global opt-out for safety checks.** Overflow and bounds checks "
"can only be bypassed per-operation via ``unsafe_*`` builtins."
msgstr ""
